# Binaries in this tree are stored inline and marked binary, on purpose.
#
# LFS: pointers are not materialised inside the Space container. An LFS-tracked PDF
# arrives as a 130-byte text file, pdfplumber reports "No /Root object! - Is this really
# a PDF?", the warm thread dies, and /api/households answers []. That is what this branch
# shipped at fc6b735. The pack documents are ~27 KB each, so there is nothing to gain by
# indirecting them and a working demo to lose.
#
# -text: without it git treats a PDF as text on a CRLF platform and rewrites its line
# endings on checkout, which corrupts it in a different way for the same end result.
*.pdf -text
*.xlsx -text
*.png -text
*.zip -text
